        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>May 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">B. H. Gotthelf</persName></p>
		<pb n="Envelope"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Walnut St No 371</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><placeName>Louisville&#44; Ky.</placeName> <date>May 25&#44; 1853</date>.</p>
			<p>Most honored <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I regret with all my heart&#44; that I had to delay my answer<lb/> to you so long&#44; and even now&#44; I am not in a position to write to you in<lb/> much detail as I should like. In the month before the last&#44; I went to the<lb/> post&#45;office&#44; and after several inquiries&#44; I received six numbers which<lb/> had not been delivered. Every one of them had had the address torn off<lb/> But who was it who had not received them&#63; I&#44; therefore&#44; waited several more<lb/> weeks for the last number&#44; and&#44; several days later&#44; upon receiving my<lb/> own&#44; I found only three left over&#44; but also without address. Since<lb/> I have acquired two new subscribers&#44; whose names I shall write<lb/> below&#44; I gave them two of these copies. Later&#44; I saw nothing until<lb/> yesterday&#44; when I again found five copies and two exemplars<lb/> &#8220;Obligation of the Sabbath&#8221; Of these five copies&#44; only three had<lb/> addresses&#44; namely&#44; <persName>Israel Hyman</persName>&#44; <persName>L. Bach</persName>&#44; and <persName>Sol. Simmons</persName>&#44;<lb/> the last&#44; as I have recently found out&#44; is now in <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>&#44; then<lb/> I think I can transmit this copy to him. As I wrote to you in<lb/> that letter you have not yet received&#44; the following have discontinued&#58;&#8212;<lb/> <persName>Abraham Din Kelsfial</persName>&#44; <persName>Goldberg</persName>&#44; <persName>Mark</persName>&#44; <persName>Mark</persName>&#44; <persName>Rosenberg</persName>&#44; <persName>Sale</persName>&#44; <persName>Hy<lb/>man</persName>&#44; <persName>Zilberman</persName>&#44; <persName>Uhlman</persName>&#44; <persName>E. Bamberger</persName>&#44; <persName>Moses Lieberman</persName>&#44; and<lb/> if I am not mistaken&#44; <persName>J. Lieber</persName>. You see&#44; therefore&#44; that almost all<lb/> your subscribers here&#44; while they do not look down upon your<lb/> periodical&#44; hate to give up the &#36;3. Since I received altogether five<lb/> copies which have not been called for&#44; I cannot tell you in detail<lb/> up to the present moment. For the same reason&#44; I have not yet collected<lb/> much. For I should very much like to see&#44; the economical gentlemen<lb/> accepting the new copies before they pay for the old&#8212;and thus become <add>&#63;</add><lb/>......Believe me&#44; dear <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName> that I have taken a great deal of<lb/> trouble with these people&#44; as much as you yourself would have taken&#44; but<lb/> not I nor even our teacher <persName>Moses</persName> could change these people. As I<lb/> told you&#44; I have two new subscribers&#8212;<persName>B. Myer</persName>&#44; <placeName>Hodgensville&#44; Ky.<lb/> Larue&#44; Ct.</placeName>&#44; and <persName>S. Oberndorfer</persName>&#44; <placeName>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> St. between Market &#38; Jefferson</placeName>.<lb/> Please send the new copies to their address. After receipt of the next issue<lb/> I shall unhesitatingly collect and send it to you as soon and as<lb/> much as possible. I should very much like to write some pleas<add>&#63;</add><lb/> news to you&#44; but the circumstances&#44; as you will see&#44; do not per<lb/>mit it. Perhaps in my next letter&#44; I&#39;ll be able to do so. My<lb/> wife and children send kindest greetings. Your most devoted<lb/> servant and friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">B. H. Gotthelf</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
